our app. Learn how to use Core Location Conditions to describe and track the state of events in your app, and find out how you can better respond to transitions in your apps through Swift semantics and improved reliability.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23-10147-Meet-Core-Location-Monitor","role":"sampleCode"},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc22/10056":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc22\/10056","title":"Compose custom layouts with SwiftUI - WWDC22","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Compose custom layouts with SwiftUI - WWDC22"}],"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc22\/10056"},"https://devstreaming-cdn.apple.com/videos/wwdc/2018/235gkyrtsva0gy/235/235_uikit_apps_for_every_size_and_shape.pdf":{"url":"https:\/\/devstreaming-cdn.apple.com\/videos\/wwdc\/2018\/235gkyrtsva0gy\/235\/235_uikit_apps_for_every_size_and_shape.pdf","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"UIKit: Apps for Every Size and Shape - WWDC18","type":"text"}],"type":"link","title":"UIKit: Apps for Every Size and Shape - WWDC18","identifier":"https:\/\/devstreaming-cdn.apple.com\/videos\/wwdc\/2018\/235gkyrtsva0gy\/235\/235_uikit_apps_for_every_size_and_shape.pdf"},"https://x.com/mortengregersen":{"type":"link","title":"X\/Twitter","url":"https:\/\/x.com\/mortengregersen","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"X\/Twitter"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/x.com\/mortengregersen"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes"},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc23/10032?time=81":{"type":"link","title":"1:21 - Overview","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc23\/10032?time=81","identifier":"http